Two agents — a first-semester nursing student in an ambulance and an ER doctor at the hospital — communicate over radio to save critically ill patients. Every word sent costs {{ seconds_per_token }} simulated seconds. If total radio time exceeds a patient's time budget, the patient dies.

Five patients arrive across five rounds, with progressively larger time budgets. Early patients have extremely tight budgets (~{{ patient_cases[0].time_budget_seconds }}s) that are nearly impossible with normal language, forcing agents to develop compressed communication patterns.

The nursing student observes symptoms and reports to the doctor in plain language. The doctor diagnoses remotely and gives simple treatment instructions. A live patient monitor sends real-time status updates as time runs out.